<article xmlns:ali="http://www.niso.org/schemas/ali/1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" article-type="abstract"><?properties open_access?><front><journal-meta><journal-id journal-id-type="nlm-ta">Orthop J Sports Med</journal-id><journal-id journal-id-type="iso-abbrev">Orthop J Sports Med</journal-id><journal-id journal-id-type="publisher-id">OJS</journal-id><journal-id journal-id-type="hwp">spojs</journal-id><journal-title-group><journal-title>Orthopaedic Journal of Sports Medicine</journal-title></journal-title-group><issn pub-type="epub">2325-9671</issn><publisher><publisher-name>SAGE Publications</publisher-name><publisher-loc>Sage CA: Los Angeles, CA</publisher-loc></publisher></journal-meta><article-meta><article-id pub-id-type="pmc">4597660</article-id><article-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1177/2325967114S00163</article-id><article-id pub-id-type="publisher-id">10.1177_2325967114S00163</article-id><article-categories><subj-group subj-group-type="heading"><subject>Article</subject></subj-group></article-categories><title-group><article-title>Epicondylitis Band or Corticosteroid Injection for Lateral Epicondylitis Treatment?</article-title></title-group><contrib-group><contrib contrib-type="author"><name><surname>Allahverdi</surname><given-names>Ertu&#x0011f;rul</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff1-2325967114S00163">1</xref></contrib><contrib contrib-type="author"><name><surname>Allahverdi</surname><given-names>T&#x000fc;lay Diken</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff2-2325967114S00163">2</xref></contrib><contrib contrib-type="author"><name><surname>T&#x000fc;rkta&#x0015f;</surname><given-names>U&#x0011f;ur</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff3-2325967114S00163">3</xref></contrib></contrib-group><aff id="aff1-2325967114S00163"><label>1</label>Kars Devlet Hastanesi Ortopedi ve Travmatoloji, Kars, TURKEY</aff><aff id="aff2-2325967114S00163"><label>2</label>Kafkas &#x000dc;niversitesi T&#x00131;p Fak&#x000fc;ltesi Genel Cerrahi, Kars, TURKEY</aff><aff id="aff3-2325967114S00163"><label>3</label>Turgut &#x000d6;zal Hastanesi Ortopedi ve Travmatoloji, Ankara, TURKEY</aff><pub-date pub-type="epub"><day>1</day><month>12</month><year>2014</year></pub-date><pub-date pub-type="collection"><month>11</month><year>2014</year></pub-date><volume>2</volume><issue>3 Suppl</issue><issue-title>12th TUSYAD (Turkish Society of Sports Traumatology, Arthroscopy, and Knee Surgery) Congress Abstracts</issue-title><elocation-id>2325967114S00163</elocation-id><permissions><copyright-statement>&#x000a9; The Author(s) 2014</copyright-statement><copyright-year>2014</copyright-year><copyright-holder content-type="sage">SAGE Publications</copyright-holder><license license-type="creative-commons" xlink:href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0/"><license-p>This open-access article is published and distributed under the Creative Commons Attribution - NonCommercial - No Derivatives License (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0/">http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0/</ext-link>), which permits the noncommercial use, distribution, and reproduction of the article in any medium, provided the original author and source are credited. You may not alter, transform, or build upon this article without the permission of the Author(s). For reprints and permission queries, please visit SAGE&#x02019;s Web site at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.sagepub.com/journalsPermissions.nav">http://www.sagepub.com/journalsPermissions.nav</ext-link>.</license-p></license></permissions><abstract><sec><title>Objectives:</title><p>Comparison of the short and medium-term results of the epicondylitis brace with corticosteroid and local anesthetic injections for lateral epicondylitis.</p></sec><sec><title>Methods:</title><p>This was a retrospective and comparative study for the treatment of acute lateral epicondylitis. The patient groups A and B received two different treatments. There were 151 patients in Group A and 205 patients in Group B. Group A received the epicondylitis brace and Group B corticosteroid and local anesthetic injections. Both groups were also given stretch exercises and nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs. Patients were assessed at weeks 1, 4, 12, and 24 and the Quick DASH scoring was performed on weeks 12 and 24.</p></sec><sec><title>Results:</title><p>At the 3rd month of treatment, Group A showed recovery rates of moderate, good and full in 18.5%, 32.5% and 30.5% respectively while these rates were 33.2%, 13.7% and 25.4% in Group B. The same rates at the end of months 6 were 17.2%, 41.1% and 17.2% in Group A and 28.3%, 1% and 17.2% in Group B.</p></sec><sec><title>Conclusion:</title><p>Combined treatment (physical therapy, nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs) with an epicondylitis brace was more effective than combined treatment with steroid and local anesthetic injections in acute lateral epicondylitis.</p></sec></abstract></article-meta></front></article>